cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NA, cs.SI

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with regularization methods in machine learning. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as machine learning is a subfield of AI. The paper mentions the application of regularization methods to multi-task learning, which suggests it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper uses principles from matrix theory, which suggests it could also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
